## DTO (Data Transfer Object)

DTO is a design pattern used to transfer data between different layers of an application.

    UI <-> Controller <-> Service <-> DTO <-> Database

A DTO usually contains only data members and minimal logic. 
It helps separate business logic from data representation and improves code organization.

Benefits of DTO:
- Reduces coupling between layers
- Simplifies data transfer
- Improves maintainability
- Commonly used with Repository, Service, and MVC patterns

In modern C++, DTOs are typically implemented using simple structs or lightweight classes.

DTO is commonly used in
    REST API response objects
    JSON serialization
    SQLite data transfer
    Microservices
    Game server packets
    Network messaging
    GUI <-> backend communication

DTO helps
    separate UI and logic
    avoid exposing internal classes
    simplify serialization
    transfer data safely
    improve architecture

DTO objects usually
    contain only data
    have little or no business logic
    are lightweight
    help separate layers cleanly